      "content": "Here are some dialogue ideas capturing the deep hatred prevalent in that era: one character could sneer, \"Y'all better know who this land belongs to,\" while another points a knife demanding the family get off his porch immediately. The aggressors might mock their language by calling them \" straners from fickle lands\" while threatening to rusticate them into the slums if they don't leave. Such raw hostility forces your characters to confront the systemic violence and inescapable racism they would face daily as outsiders.",
